worldMap.svg
============

Source : https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:ISO_3166-1_Alpha-2_map.svg
Author : Wikimedia Commons user "Белозёров Никита"
License: Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International
         (CC BY-SA 4.0)
         https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

This SVG is bundled unmodified as `worldMap.svg`. It carries the
original authorship metadata inside the file. The CC BY-SA 4.0 share-
alike clause applies to the SVG itself: any modifications to
`worldMap.svg` must be released under the same license. The
surrounding project code (JS, CSS, HTML) does not become a derivative
work merely by loading the SVG — this is "mere aggregation," not a
derivative, so the rest of the repository keeps its own license.

Used by the flagQuiz Europe-and-beyond contour map feature: paths are
ID'd by ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 lowercase country code. Per-variant viewBox
crops at runtime focus the same asset on each continent's bounds.
